---
import '../styles/global.css';
import TBCalculator from '../components/TBCalculator.tsx';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="TB Drug Dosage Calculator — calculates Pyrazinamide and Ethambutol dosing using Lean Body Weight (James Equation)."
    />
    <title>TB Drug Dosage Calculator – Pyrazinamide and Ethambutol dose calculator</title>
  </head>
  <body class="bg-white text-gray-900 antialiased">
    <main class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 py-10">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-extrabold tracking-tight">TB Drug Dosage Calculator</h1>

      <p class="mt-6 text-[15px] font-bold">
        Disclaimer: Not intended to be official medical advice. Please consult your physician before
        starting any new medications.
      </p>

      <p class="mt-4 text-[15px] font-bold text-red-600">
        Site rebuilt on 06/25/2026 using more appropriate front end(Migrated from wordpress to a basic
        React/TS site). The underlying logic should all be identical so there shouldn't be any bugs,
        but if you notice any or have any suggestions for updates please email me at <a
          class="underline"
          href="mailto:mannevijay@gmail.com">mannevijay@gmail.com</a
        >.
      </p>

      <p class="mt-5 text-[15px]">
        Calculates drug dosing for Pyrazinamide and Ethambutol using Lean Body Weight(James Equation)
      </p>

      <!-- Interactive calculator (React island) -->
      <section class="mt-2">
        <TBCalculator client:load />
      </section>

      <!-- Preserved intended-use / clinical guidance text -->
      <p class="mt-8 text-[15px]">
        Therapeutic drug monitoring to guide dose adjustment is recommended in the follow
        circumstances:<br />
        — Patients with LBW &gt;90<br />
        — Patients with suspected or proven malabsorption<br />
        — Other forms of renal replacement (e.g. peritoneal dialysis), doses are administered 3 times
        per week in conjunction with therapeutic drug monitoring
      </p>

      <p class="mt-5 text-[15px]">
        If the patient&rsquo;s Serum Creatinine(SCr) suggests eGFR is less than 30 (if input is SCr,
        eGFR calculated per Cockroft-Gault equation), OR if the patient is on renal replacement
        therapy, the dosing is the same mg per dose, but given less frequently according to method of
        renal replacement. If on intermittent hemodialysis, doses are timed after each HD session. For
        other forms of renal replacement (e.g. peritoneal dialysis), the doses are timed 3 times a week
      </p>

      <hr class="mx-auto my-8 w-40 border-gray-200" />

      <p class="text-[15px]">
        <a
          class="text-blue-700 underline-offset-2 hover:underline"
          href="/references">Calculator Logic and References</a
        >
      </p>
      <p class="mt-5 text-[15px]">
        <a
          class="text-blue-700 underline-offset-2 hover:underline"
          href="mailto:mannevijay@gmail.com">For comments, questions or suggestions</a
        >
      </p>
    </main>

    <footer class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 py-8 text-xs text-gray-500">
      TB Drug Dosage Calculator
    </footer>
  </body>
</html>
